TASK 1
Date: 19-01-2026
=================

TOPIC: E-RUPEE (DIGITAL RUPEE)
=============================


1. Definition
-------------
E-Rupee (e₹) is India’s official digital currency issued by the
Reserve Bank of India (RBI).

It is also known as Central Bank Digital Currency (CBDC).


2. What Exactly is E-Rupee?
--------------------------
- Digital form of Indian Rupee (₹)
- Issued and controlled by RBI
- Has the same value as physical cash
  ₹1 e₹ = ₹1 physical rupee
- Exists only in digital form (no paper or coin)


3. Types of E-Rupee
------------------

3.1 e₹-W (Wholesale):
- Used by banks and financial institutions

Purpose:
- Inter-bank settlements
- Government securities transactions

Benefits:
- Faster settlements
- Lower transaction cost


3.2 e₹-R (Retail):
- Used by the general public

Purpose:
- Daily payments (similar to UPI)
- Person-to-Person (P2P) payments
- Merchant payments

Works through:
- RBI-approved digital wallets


4. How E-Rupee Works
-------------------
1. RBI issues the e-rupee
2. Banks distribute it to users
3. Users store it in a digital wallet
4. Payments occur directly without bank settlement delay


5. E-Rupee vs UPI vs Cryptocurrency
----------------------------------

Feature              E-Rupee        UPI              Cryptocurrency
Issued by            RBI            Banks            Private networks
Legal Tender         Yes            No               No
Government Backed    Yes            No               No
Value Stability      Stable         Stable           Highly volatile
Blockchain / DLT     Yes (DLT)       No               Yes
Internet Required    Not always     Yes              Yes


6. Key Features of E-Rupee
-------------------------
- Government-backed digital money
- Secure and tamper-proof
- No interest (similar to cash)
- Offline payments possible
- Programmable money (future scope)


7. Why India Introduced E-Rupee
------------------------------
- Reduce cash handling costs
- Prevent counterfeit currency
- Enabl
